MALALANE &#8211; A man was arrested with a 5,9-kilogram rhino horn in his possession on Thursday. According to Hawks spokesman Capt Dineo Sekgotodi, police arrested a Mozambican male (28) at around 23:30 on the N4 near Kaapmuiden after receiving a tip-off.The accused&#8217;s white Toyota Corolla was pulled off the road and searched by police when the horn was discovered.Sekgotodi said the horn has a street value of R383 500.The rhino horn police confiscated.The suspect appeared in the Malalane Magistrate&#8217;s Court on Monday. He had not been identified at the time of going to press.Read more here: Suspects linked to rhino poaching arrested